{
  "page": "Tree of Crowns",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Tree of Crowns</b> is located in the <a href=\"/index.php/Disputed_Lands\" title=\"Disputed Lands\">Disputed Lands</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_258_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">258&#160;AC</a>, nine <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaws\" title=\"Outlaws\">outlaws</a>, exiles, <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirates</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellsword</a> captains—remembered by history as the \"<a href=\"/index.php/Band_of_Nine\" title=\"Band of Nine\">Band of Nine</a>\"—met beneath the Tree of Crowns as to form an alliance, swearing to aid each other in conquering kingdoms for each of the nine members.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tree_of_Crowns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Tree of Crowns may be a reference by <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> to the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oath_of_the_Peach_Garden\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Oath of the Peach Garden\">Oath of the Peach Garden</a>, a fictional event in the 14th century Chinese historical novel <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romance_of_the_Three_Kingdoms\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Romance of the Three Kingdoms\">Romance of the Three Kingdoms</a></i>. Martin stated he played \"obsessively\" the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romance_of_the_Three_Kingdoms_(video_game)\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Romance of the Three Kingdoms (video game)\">1985 video game</a> inspired by the novel.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Chapter drafts dating back to October 2003 and June 2004 describe the Tree of Crowns as an apple tree.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tree_of_Crowns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Not a Blog\">Not a Blog</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://grrm.livejournal.com/372179.html?thread=19170515#t19170515\">Ten Thousand Ships (Comment by GRRM)</a> (May 26, 2014)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Reddit: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/asoiaf/comments/10cq27q/spoilers_extended_secrets_of_the_cushing_library/\">Secrets of the Cushing Library: The Grand Finale by u/gsteff</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404195831\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.020 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.040 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 135/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8637/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 556/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 158/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1458/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.5 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   34.922      1 -total\n 77.79%   27.167      1 Template:Date\n 14.38%    5.021      1 Template:Ref\n  8.97%    3.131      1 Template:Ref/core\n  5.36%    1.873      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:24370-0!canonical and timestamp 20260404195831 and revision id 324590\n -->\n",
